{"build_type":"library","description":"Return the default row budget for a single-directory listing: the maximum number of entry rows a full-output listing tool emits before it stops and reports output_budget_exceeded (a LOUD structured truncation, never a silent black-box or a biased partial pretending to be complete). A deterministic COUNT budget (not a wall-clock timeout) keeps the verdict reproducible. Defined as a function (not a global initializer — lowering ignores global inits) so the single source of truth for the limit lives here; callers that accept a per-request override compare against this default. Reused by list_directory_entries_with_metadata.","module_name":"default-directory-listing-budget-budget","package_name":"default-directory-listing-budget-budget","function_definitions":{"default-directory-listing-budget-budget":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"budget","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2000},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"budget"}}]}}}